title: I created a new branch on my remote github. Now I am on my local machine, in...

parts: I created a new branch on my remote github. Now I am on my local machine, in WSL. How do I fetch that branch and switch into it?

From your WSL repo directory:

```bash
# 1) Update your remotes / fetch new branches
git fetch origin

# 2) See the remote branches (optional)
git branch -r

# 3) Create a local branch that tracks the remote one, and switch to it
git switch -c <branch-name> --track origin/<branch-name>
```

If you’re on an older Git version that doesn’t have `git switch`, use:

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout -b <branch-name> origin/<branch-name>
```

Notes:
- Replace `origin` if your remote is named differently (`git remote -v` to check).
- If you *already* have a local branch with that name, just do:
  ```bash
  git fetch origin
  git switch <branch-name>
  ```
